text: ACT/IT Infrastructure monitors traffic on the network for the purpose of maintaining proper network function
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall
University Housing monitors only the amount of traffic
H323 video conferencing is allowed by the University firewall
There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
IMAP and secure IMAP are allowed by the University firewall
The UC Davis network is continually scanned for prohibited activities and network threats.
HTTP and HTTPS are allowed by the University firewall
All network traffic passing in or out of Brown's network is monitored by intrusion detection system for signs of compromises
RHIT-OPEN will work in labs, classrooms and residence halls but does not allow the user to access the internal Rose-Hulman network
Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
Currently, the University of Illinois does not have any rate limits set in place
